<recipe>
<title>
Cinnamon Apples
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
COOK TIME: 10 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 20 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: apples, cinnamon
SERVINGS: 6 servings
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="0.25 Cup">Butter</ingredient><ingredient amount="4.0 Inch">Apple</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 Cup">Cold Water</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5 Cup">Sugar</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add apple slices.
Cook, stirring regularly, until apples are almost tender, about 6-7 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; add to skillet. Stir to combine.
Stir in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring regularly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and any other desired flavorings.
Serve warm.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>